claim.claim-text:
1. An adjustable eye shield comprising: 
a flexible, transparent material adapted to fit over the eyes and at least partially wrap around the face of a user, the material divided into a plurality of regions, comprising at least a left region, a right region, and a central region; 
at least one slit in both the left and the right regions, the slit extending fully across the region thus subdividing the left region into a first and a second section and subdividing the right region into a first and a second section; 
at least one hole in each of the first sections of the left and the right regions; and 
an adjustable fastener for fastening the eye shield to the head of the user having a plurality of ends, at least one end of the fastener passes through at least one of the holes in the first section of the right region, traverses the slit in the right region, and is fastened to the second section of the right region, at least one other end of the fastener passes through at least one of the holes in the first section of the left region, traverses the slit in the left region, and is secured to the second section of the left region; 
wherein the first and second sections of each of the left and right regions are adapted to slide one over the other when the adjustable fastener is pulled.

14. An adjustable eye shield comprising: 
a flattened, flexible, transparent sheet material divided into a plurality of regions, comprising at least a left region, a right region, and a central region; 
at least one slit extending fully across the left region subdividing the region into a first and a second section, one of the sections comprising a hole proximate to an edge and distal from the slit; 
at least one slit extending fully across the right region subdividing the region into a first and a second section, at least one of the sections comprising a hole; 
at least one hole in each of the first sections of the left and the right regions at a location distal from the central region; and 
an adjustable fastener having a plurality of ends, a separate end selected from the plurality of ends dedicated to each of the left and right regions so that the dedicated end is affixed to one of the sections within its dedicated region, traverses the slit in the same region, and passes through the hole in the remaining section opposite the slit in the same region; 
wherein by manipulation of the adjustable fastener the first and second sections of each of the left and right regions are adapted to slide one over the other causing the material to gradually bend without creasing.
